    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="206"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d206">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits 35/316a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-04T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 4, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>210. The Department is still considering the status of the two banks in
                        Argentina<note n="43" xml:id="d206fn43">Banco de la Nación and Banco de la
                        Provincia Buenos Aires.</note> as outlined in your No. 302, February 2, 5
                        p.m.,<note n="44" xml:id="d206fn44">Not printed.</note> but does not
                    contemplate action pending further developments in Argentina.</p>
                <p>Department is confident, in this connection, that you will report promptly any
                    measures to implement decree severing financial transactions with Axis and any
                    action taken by the Argentine Government to control financial transactions
                    within Argentina which may be of benefit to Axis nationals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
